    "name": "Bitcoin Explorer \u2014 /api/v1",
    "description": "Versioned REST API (`/api/v1`). Source of truth: repository `openapi.yaml`. Import this file into Postman or Bruno.\n\n**Auth:** Cookie sessions. Run **Login**; Postman persists `Set-Cookie` for `session_id`. The login **Tests** script stores `csrfToken` for mutating routes.\n\n**Machine tokens:** optional `Authorization: Bearer {{apiKeyBearer}}` (prefix `bkx_`) for scoped automation (`user:*` / `admin:*`). No CSRF when you do **not** send `session_id`. See docs/API_KEYS.md.\n\n**CSRF:** Send `X-CSRF-Token` on POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE and on **all** `/api/v1/admin/*` requests when logged in (`csrfMiddleware`). Register/login skip CSRF by design.\n\n**Probe:** Prometheus scrape is `GET /metrics` with optional `METRICS_TOKEN` \u2014 omitted here.",
